Title: The White Junk of Love, Again
Author: James, Sibyl
Subjects: American Poetry, Italian Poetry, Sonnets, French Poetry, Love Poetry
Synopsis: Poetry. In these translitics of the sonnets of sixteenth century poet Louise Labe, James's contemporary voice allows Labe's struggle with passion and eroticism to surface with new life. James creates a jazzy, tough-minded voice that is easy to imagine as that of an avant-garde poet of 1550 transported to the late 20th century--Seattle Times.
